The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, held a press briefing on June 30, 2016. He addressed a variety of topics including an incident at Andrews Air Force Base, the Brexit vote, the meeting between Attorney General Lynch and Bill Clinton, the recent terrorist attacks in Turkey and Afghanistan, and the President's views on populism and trade agreements. Earnest also discussed the President's stance on gun control and the ongoing investigation into civilian casualties caused by U.S. airstrikes. He ended the briefing by addressing transgender issues and restroom policies on federal lands and in federal buildings.